cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with video object segmentation using a novel spatio-temporal Markov Random Field (MRF) model defined over pixels, which is encoded by a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a CNN-embedded algorithm to perform approximate inference in the MRF, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with video processing (cs.MM) and modeling (cs.NE) techniques.
